Click 'play full video' to watch the video.Thai authorities have named 23-year old South African Abel Caldeira Bonito and 27-year old British national Miles Dicken Turner as being wanted in connection with the execution-style murder of Tony Kenway in Pattaya on Tuesday.According to the Daily Mail, police are reportedly investigating whether a football gambling website set up by Kenway may have caused a rift with rival firms. The father-of-four had been living in Thailand for the last seven years.In the CCTV footage, the gunman flees the scene on a motorcycle moments after the shot is fired.Thai PBS reported that Bonito was identified as the gunman from video footage while Turner had rented the bike.A Facebook page for Bonito describes him as self-employed and living in Orkney South Africa.Video courtesy the Daily Mail